    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-14T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-14T11:00:00-05:00" n="325"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">704.3335/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina (<persName corresp="#p_BRW1"
                            type="from">Bliss</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-14T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 14, 1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 12:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>56. Counselor of Uruguayan Embassy has just called informing me that he had been
                    instructed by Uruguayan Minister for Foreign Affairs to ask if this Embassy
                    would assume chargé of Uruguayan interests during interruption of diplomatic
                    relations with Argentina. I replied that I would immediately inform the
                    Government at Washington and advise of the answer received. Argentina has
                    entrusted its interests in Uruguay to the British Legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BRW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bliss</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
